\begin_inset Formula $10^{-18}$
\end_inset

cm
\begin_inset Formula $^{2}$
\end_inset

, calculate the maximum gain coefficient if the inversion is equal to the
 number density of air at STP.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The number density of air at STP (according to Wikipedia) is 
\begin_inset Formula $0.02504\times10^{21}$
\end_inset

cm
\begin_inset Formula $^{-3}$
\end_inset

.
 Assuming the inversion is the number density, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta N=0.02504\times10^{21}$
\end_inset

cm
\begin_inset Formula $^{-3}$
\end_inset

.
 The gain coefficient would be 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
g=\sigma\Delta N=10^{-18}\text{cm}^{2}(0.02504\times10^{21}\text{cm}^{-3})=25.04\text{cm}^{-1}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

